"Frol'kis V.A., Kiselev A.A., Karol' I.L.","Evaluation of anthropogenic climate changes from simulated radiative and photochemical processes in the atmosphere",1999,"Izvestiya - Atmospheric and Ocean Physics","35","4",,"401","412",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0033457266&partnerID=40&md5=4e95643584eccf685cc01085013a2454","Voeikov Main Geophysical Observatory, ul. Karbysheva 7, St. Petersburg, 194018, Russian Federation","Frol'kis, V.A., Voeikov Main Geophysical Observatory, ul. Karbysheva 7, St. Petersburg, 194018, Russian Federation; Kiselev, A.A., Voeikov Main Geophysical Observatory, ul. Karbysheva 7, St. Petersburg, 194018, Russian Federation; Karol', I.L., Voeikov Main Geophysical Observatory, ul. Karbysheva 7, St. Petersburg, 194018, Russian Federation","Changes in the radiative atmospheric conditions due to anthropogenic pollution are simulated mathematically. This simulation is used to describe the effect of anthropogenic and natural trace gases on the climate system in the past, as well as to estimate the influence of pollution on the radiative conditions in the future. A new scheme for radiative forcing computations is proposed and compared with the conventional scheme. Radiative forcing and the radiative contribution to global warming are examined depending on observed and predicted emissions of basic trace gases. Various scenarios of anthropogenic pollutant emissions and individual gaseous pollutants are estimated as sources of influence on radiative forcing and global warming.",,"anthropogenic effect; atmospheric pollution; climate change; photochemistry; radiative forcing",,,,,,"Hansen, J., Johnson, D., Lacis, A., Lebedeff, S., Lee, P., Rind, D., Russell, G., Greenhouse Impacts of Increasing Carbon Dioxide (1981) Science, 213, pp. 957-966; Ramanathan, V., Cicerone, R.J., Singh, H.B., Kiehl, J.T., Trace Gas Trends and Their Potential Role in Climate Change (1985) J. Geophys. Res., 90 (3), pp. 5547-5566; Cess, R.D., Potter, G.L.,